<TITLE> Constable suspended for harassing MP </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 12 (bdnews24.com)  Police allegedly harassed a Chittagong lawmaker on Monday as he tried to stop an expatriate being assaulted by police, witnesses said. Abdul Halim Sumon, an expatriate living in Oman, was stopped and assaulted on way to the city from the airport, the witnesses added. When M A Latif, the MP and president of the Chittagong Chamber of Commerce and Industry, who took the road, intervened, a constable misbehaved with him. When the news spread, local people tried to beat the constable, but the mob was calmed by Latif and senior police officials. "When I intervened seeing the man being harassed, the police constable misbehaved with me." Police commissioner Md Moniruzzaman, went to the scene and promised action against the police constable in question. The constable has been suspended. bdnew
